WEBVTT

1
00:01:12.657 --> 00:01:14.617
<i>Folks. we're starting our
initial descent into Austin.</i>

2
00:01:14.618 --> 00:01:16.953
<i>so we're gonna ask you to
return to your seats now.</i>

3
00:01:17.454 --> 00:01:19.998
<i>We should have you on the
ground in about 15 minutes.</i>

4
00:01:21.249 --> 00:01:22.249
<i>You okay?</i>

5
00:01:23.293 --> 00:01:25.086
<i>You sure this is a good idea?</i>

6
00:01:33.178 --> 00:01:34.678
Here you go. Bailey.

7
00:01:34.679 --> 00:01:36.138
One for you. Suz.

8
00:01:36.139 --> 00:01:37.681
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

9
00:01:37.682 --> 00:01:40.810
We could have shared
popcorn. Two is so extra.

10
00:01:49.402 --> 00:01:51.863
- You okay?
- Apparently. I'm extra.

11
00:01:52.989 --> 00:01:55.241
I've been extra eight
or nine times this week.

12
00:01:55.242 --> 00:01:57.786
I'm starting to think
of it as a compliment.

13
00:01:59.496 --> 00:02:01.373
You sure this is a good idea?

14
00:02:02.582 --> 00:02:05.377
<i>Yeah. I'm pretty sure.</i>

15
00:02:06.044 --> 00:02:08.920
I mean. separating what
they want from what you want

16
00:02:08.921 --> 00:02:13.093
from what's actually best for them
makes for a lot of tricky decisions.

17
00:02:14.010 --> 00:02:15.553
You weren't one of them.

18
00:02:15.554 --> 00:02:17.055
I find that hard to believe.

19
00:02:17.556 --> 00:02:19.933
Yeah. it's 'cause I know
something you don't know.

20
00:02:20.475 --> 00:02:21.601
Oh. yeah? What's that?

21
00:02:22.561 --> 00:02:25.689
You are absolutely gonna
be what's best for her.

22
00:02:30.110 --> 00:02:32.279
And. you know. me.

23
00:03:14.988 --> 00:03:16.197
Do you want my jacket?

24
00:03:16.990 --> 00:03:17.991
No.

25
00:03:19.951 --> 00:03:20.952
Thanks.

26
00:03:24.539 --> 00:03:25.957
Jesus.

27
00:03:28.418 --> 00:03:29.753
We're gonna figure this out.

28
00:03:30.795 --> 00:03:31.796
Uh-huh.

29
00:03:35.967 --> 00:03:37.843
I was thinking we should
start at the stadium.

30
00:03:37.844 --> 00:03:41.639
- What?
- I've been researching childhood memories.

31
00:03:41.640 --> 00:03:42.848
Okay.

32
00:03:42.849 --> 00:03:45.018
And it seems that if we go
to the stadium. it might...

33
00:03:46.102 --> 00:03:48.562
You might be able to
remember more details.

34
00:03:48.563 --> 00:03:51.607
You get this from one of your
hippie woodworking clients?

35
00:03:51.608 --> 00:03:56.654
It's wood turning. and this is a real
thing. I read about it in <i>Psych</i>...

36
00:03:56.655 --> 00:03:59.823
Please tell me this whole
adventure doesn't hinge on me

37
00:03:59.824 --> 00:04:02.326
remembering stuff from.
like. a zillion years ago.

38
00:04:02.327 --> 00:04:04.871
- Hey. y'all. Seat belts fastened?
- Yeah. they're fastened.

39
00:04:08.541 --> 00:04:10.751
I get it. I have
a teenager myself.

40
00:04:10.752 --> 00:04:11.836
I'm not hers.

41
00:04:32.357 --> 00:04:36.527
<i>Hey. it's me. Figured I
could give you a ride.</i>

42
00:04:36.528 --> 00:04:39.572
<i>But you probably already left.</i>

43
00:04:39.573 --> 00:04:42.158
You getting any service?
I still have no bars.

44
00:04:43.785 --> 00:04:45.996
- Maybe someone's tracing your phone.
- What?

45
00:04:47.539 --> 00:04:48.540
I was kidding.

46
00:04:49.291 --> 00:04:51.459
Try clicking it in and
out of airplane mode.

47
00:04:54.713 --> 00:04:56.715
You didn't miss
anything. by the way.

48
00:04:57.215 --> 00:04:58.216
Dad didn't call.

49
00:05:04.055 --> 00:05:05.055
Welcome to Town Hotel.

50
00:05:05.056 --> 00:05:08.184
- You ladies need a bellhop?
- We're good. thanks.

51
00:05:25.035 --> 00:05:26.036
You coming?

52
00:05:29.080 --> 00:05:32.459
Go ahead. I'll be right
there. Just get in line.

53
00:05:47.140 --> 00:05:50.434
<i>Hey. it's Jake. I need to talk to
you. and the sooner. the better.</i>

54
00:05:50.435 --> 00:05:52.394
<i>The FBI wants to set
up formal interview.</i>

55
00:05:52.395 --> 00:05:54.855
<i>which means either they know more
about Owen than they're saying.</i>

56
00:05:54.856 --> 00:05:57.441
<i>or they think they
have something on you.</i>

57
00:05:57.442 --> 00:05:59.652
<i>Point is. I don't get you
in front of them soon.</i>

58
00:05:59.653 --> 00:06:01.487
<i>they're gonna start treating
you like a hostile witness.</i>

59
00:06:01.488 --> 00:06:04.491
<i>So I need you to call
me back. like. now.</i>

60
00:06:36.189 --> 00:06:38.941
- Who called?
- Just a friend in LA.

61
00:06:38.942 --> 00:06:40.734
- A friend?
- Hi. y'all!

62
00:06:40.735 --> 00:06:42.903
Welcome to Austin. What
can I help you with?

63
00:06:42.904 --> 00:06:45.240
Just checking in for Max Parnes.

64
00:06:46.908 --> 00:06:49.327
Did you bring wigs and
a fake mustache too?

65
00:07:46.009 --> 00:07:49.220
So. he has been our
team mascot since 1916.

66
00:07:49.221 --> 00:07:53.224
Pop quiz. Does anyone know what
the mascot was before Bevo?

67
00:07:53.225 --> 00:07:54.976
I think it was a dog.

68
00:07:56.061 --> 00:07:57.436
Eighth largest
stadium in the world.

69
00:07:57.437 --> 00:07:59.396
- At least that's what Wikipedia says.
- An owl.

70
00:07:59.397 --> 00:08:01.107
Wow. are you on a TLC show?

71
00:08:01.608 --> 00:08:03.108
What's going on over here. sir?

72
00:08:03.109 --> 00:08:04.777
Yeah. I see you with
the Rice Owls shirt.

73
00:08:04.778 --> 00:08:06.111
What's going on there?

74
00:08:06.112 --> 00:08:08.155
Who let this guy
on the tour. huh?

75
00:08:08.156 --> 00:08:09.241
Let's latch on with them.

76
00:08:10.242 --> 00:08:13.160
- It's hot and this is dumb.
- Okay. maybe. but...

77
00:08:13.161 --> 00:08:15.287
Just saying. this all
feels like a waste of time.

78
00:08:15.288 --> 00:08:16.957
Would you rather be in school?

79
00:08:18.166 --> 00:08:20.668
Will you just try coming
inside? Can we start there?

80
00:08:20.669 --> 00:08:21.795
Do I have a choice?

81
00:08:22.796 --> 00:08:24.964
Yes. Always. With
me. you always do.

82
00:08:24.965 --> 00:08:28.218
All righty. and if you follow me.
we'll make our way to the field.

83
00:08:30.136 --> 00:08:34.224
That means you too. Mr. Owl. I'll show
you what a real stadium looks like.

84
00:08:37.936 --> 00:08:41.105
That big enclosure y'all saw on
the way in is where we keep Bevo.

85
00:08:41.106 --> 00:08:46.403
So I'm supposed to... What? Close
my eyes and chant something?

86
00:08:47.737 --> 00:08:50.949
The articles I read just said
to try to take the place in.

87
00:08:51.449 --> 00:08:54.785
Just feel what it's like now so you
can remember what it was like then.

88
00:08:54.786 --> 00:08:56.371
Where'd you get these articles?

89
00:08:56.955 --> 00:08:58.373
<i>Psychology Today</i>.

90
00:08:59.207 --> 00:09:01.585
Max sent an article in
<i>Scientific American</i>.

91
00:09:34.993 --> 00:09:38.496
I'm not feeling
anything. Shocker. right?

92
00:09:40.540 --> 00:09:42.124
Maybe we should
try somewhere else.

93
00:09:42.125 --> 00:09:44.418
It's the eighth largest
stadium in the world. Hannah.

94
00:09:44.419 --> 00:09:46.086
There are thousands
of seats here.

95
00:09:46.087 --> 00:09:48.381
- I'm not saying we should try all of them.
- Good.

96
00:10:49.067 --> 00:10:50.485
Bailey?

97
00:10:55.073 --> 00:10:56.908
I think it was. I...

98
00:10:57.909 --> 00:10:59.619
- I think I was...
- You were here.

99
00:11:00.370 --> 00:11:01.371
Yeah.

100
00:11:03.039 --> 00:11:05.584
But my dad. he was
wearing a suit.

101
00:11:06.209 --> 00:11:07.376
At a football game?

102
00:11:07.377 --> 00:11:11.756
Yeah. it's weird. right? I...
It doesn't make any sense.

103
00:11:12.465 --> 00:11:16.635
But it's funny. I remember
being kind of uncomfortable too.

104
00:11:16.636 --> 00:11:20.056
like. itchy. like
I was in a dress.

105
00:11:20.974 --> 00:11:22.433
You said you were
visiting friends here.

106
00:11:22.434 --> 00:11:26.562
Were you coming from somewhere
else. a party. or something?

107
00:11:26.563 --> 00:11:31.359
I think we were at a
party. A wedding. maybe?

108
00:11:32.068 --> 00:11:34.112
I think we walked
here from there.

109
00:11:34.613 --> 00:11:36.072
- From the wedding?
- Yeah.

110
00:11:38.283 --> 00:11:41.076
No. I... I'm not...

111
00:11:41.077 --> 00:11:42.287
I'm not sure.

112
00:11:46.458 --> 00:11:48.459
<i>Two in section 40-C.</i>

113
00:11:48.460 --> 00:11:50.419
- Yeah. I see them.
- Let's go.

114
00:11:50.420 --> 00:11:52.671
<i>If you walked here. the
church could be close.</i>

115
00:11:52.672 --> 00:11:54.341
Okay. but I...

116
00:11:55.050 --> 00:11:56.051
What?

117
00:11:56.760 --> 00:11:59.179
My dad. it was like he loved it.

118
00:12:00.180 --> 00:12:02.556
- The game?
- Yeah. The game. the team. the stadium.

119
00:12:02.557 --> 00:12:04.391
All of it. But...

120
00:12:04.392 --> 00:12:05.894
Your dad doesn't like football.

121
00:12:07.187 --> 00:12:08.188
No.

122
00:12:19.032 --> 00:12:20.408
Okay. great. Thanks. guys.

123
00:12:22.494 --> 00:12:24.662
Hey. Making any progress?

124
00:12:24.663 --> 00:12:27.414
<i>Maybe. Bailey thinks she
was here for a wedding.</i>

125
00:12:27.415 --> 00:12:28.791
I thought if I can
find the church.

126
00:12:28.792 --> 00:12:31.252
I might be able to figure
out whose wedding it was.

127
00:12:31.253 --> 00:12:34.213
- and maybe talk to them and...
- Okay. How can I help?

128
00:12:34.214 --> 00:12:37.925
My Internet is spotty. Can you get me
a list of all the churches near DKR?

129
00:12:37.926 --> 00:12:39.635
Bailey thinks they walked here.

130
00:12:39.636 --> 00:12:42.137
so maybe all the churches
in a two mile radius?

131
00:12:42.138 --> 00:12:44.014
Slow down. Slow down. Let
me get to my desk. okay?

132
00:12:44.015 --> 00:12:45.225
<i>Yeah. yeah. Thanks.</i>

133
00:12:47.602 --> 00:12:50.854
<i>Okay. I'm at my computer. All
churches within two miles of DKR?</i>

134
00:12:50.855 --> 00:12:54.567
And a list of the weekend home
games during the 2011 season.

135
00:12:54.568 --> 00:12:56.610
- Would that be hard to find?
- You know how many sports sites

136
00:12:56.611 --> 00:12:58.445
are out there for all
the fantasy stat nerds?

137
00:12:58.446 --> 00:13:00.573
<i>Hi. I'm Hannah. Have we met?</i>

138
00:13:00.574 --> 00:13:02.366
Okay. a lot. all
right? There are a lot.

139
00:13:02.367 --> 00:13:03.742
<i>Okay. So not hard?</i>

140
00:13:03.743 --> 00:13:06.620
- Nope. Just 2011?
- <i>I think so.</i>

141
00:13:06.621 --> 00:13:08.831
Bailey's pretty sure her
mom was at the wedding.

142
00:13:08.832 --> 00:13:12.585
So. the game had
to be before 2012.

143
00:13:12.586 --> 00:13:14.962
And in 2010. she would've
been barely three. so...

144
00:13:14.963 --> 00:13:17.423
So 2011's the only year
she would remember.

145
00:13:17.424 --> 00:13:19.384
- <i>Yeah. I think so.</i>
- Okay. Got it.

146
00:13:20.218 --> 00:13:22.762
Hey. Han. It's
Max. How's Bailey?

147
00:13:23.889 --> 00:13:28.727
Not great. You think I'm crazy for
bringing her down here. don't you?

148
00:13:29.227 --> 00:13:31.103
I think it's much better
you're out of town.

149
00:13:31.104 --> 00:13:32.730
Story's only getting worse here.

150
00:13:32.731 --> 00:13:33.814
<i>Worse how?</i>

151
00:13:33.815 --> 00:13:36.442
Well. my sources are saying that
the scope of the investigation

152
00:13:36.443 --> 00:13:37.985
<i>is changing by the hour.</i>

153
00:13:37.986 --> 00:13:40.780
<i>Last I heard. all senior
staff could be indicted.</i>

154
00:13:41.781 --> 00:13:44.200
<i>I haven't heard Owen's
name yet. but it's</i>...

155
00:13:45.410 --> 00:13:47.930
- <i>I'm assuming. you know. he's...</i>
- Guys. I gotta call you back.

156
00:13:48.663 --> 00:13:49.663
Bailey?

157
00:13:51.541 --> 00:13:52.541
Bailey?

158
00:14:01.051 --> 00:14:02.135
Bailey!

159
00:15:04.698 --> 00:15:06.116
Jesus.

160
00:15:06.700 --> 00:15:08.158
I had no idea where you went.

161
00:15:08.159 --> 00:15:11.620
I texted you. You were on the phone.
I texted you I was coming in here.

162
00:15:11.621 --> 00:15:14.415
Bailey. it doesn't matter. You
cannot disappear like that.

163
00:15:14.416 --> 00:15:15.583
Okay. Can you just chill?

164
00:15:15.584 --> 00:15:19.044
Bailey. listen to me. With everything
going on. you have to stay with me.

165
00:15:19.045 --> 00:15:20.755
We need to stay together.

166
00:15:30.557 --> 00:15:32.726
I was supposed to
block my solo today.

167
00:15:34.644 --> 00:15:36.478
I had all these ideas.

168
00:15:36.479 --> 00:15:39.273
And I... I'd started
talking to Mr. K. about it.

169
00:15:39.274 --> 00:15:43.069
and he kept saying he was really
looking forward to it and...

170
00:15:46.531 --> 00:15:49.117
guess that's a stupid
thing to care about now.

171
00:15:49.993 --> 00:15:51.119
No. it's not.

172
00:15:52.579 --> 00:15:56.333
And we'll get back to that.
Bailey. All of it. I promise.

173
00:15:58.793 --> 00:16:00.128
What if he doesn't come back?

174
00:16:01.338 --> 00:16:02.380
He's coming back.

175
00:16:04.758 --> 00:16:05.842
How do you know?

176
00:16:06.509 --> 00:16:08.511
You're here. for starters.

177
00:16:13.433 --> 00:16:16.937
That's Jules. She's working
on the list of churches.

178
00:16:17.979 --> 00:16:19.856
Let's take it one
step at a time.

179
00:16:23.944 --> 00:16:25.819
<i>Hey. everything okay?</i>

180
00:16:25.820 --> 00:16:27.279
Yeah. Sorry about that.

181
00:16:27.280 --> 00:16:30.115
- No worries. I just sent you a list.
- <i>Great.</i>

182
00:16:30.116 --> 00:16:32.117
<i>You have to know.
there are a bunch.</i>

183
00:16:32.118 --> 00:16:34.370
That's all right. I think we
could use the distraction.

184
00:16:34.371 --> 00:16:35.455
<i>Okay. well.</i>

185
00:16:36.581 --> 00:16:38.458
- keep me posted. all right?
- <i>Thanks.</i>

186
00:16:42.045 --> 00:16:43.964
This isn't gonna get any
better for them. is it?

187
00:16:45.131 --> 00:16:46.299
Not anytime soon.

188
00:16:51.304 --> 00:16:52.722
First one's just down the block.

189
00:16:53.348 --> 00:16:54.348
How many are there?

190
00:16:54.349 --> 00:16:56.141
There's about a dozen.
but only three or four

191
00:16:56.142 --> 00:16:59.854
that are a reasonable walk to the
stadium. especially with a four-year-old.

192
00:17:03.024 --> 00:17:04.776
- You gonna get that?
- Yeah.

193
00:17:07.279 --> 00:17:08.404
Hello?

194
00:17:08.405 --> 00:17:09.613
<i>Hannah? It's me.</i>

195
00:17:11.824 --> 00:17:13.242
Not Dad. huh?

196
00:17:13.243 --> 00:17:14.578
Hannah. you there?

197
00:17:15.078 --> 00:17:17.621
- <i>Hey. Belle.</i>
- Hannah. I've been trying to reach you.

198
00:17:17.622 --> 00:17:19.415
<i>It's not really a
great time to talk.</i>

199
00:17:19.416 --> 00:17:21.708
Yes. I know. That's
why we're calling.

200
00:17:21.709 --> 00:17:22.794
She's on.

201
00:17:24.963 --> 00:17:25.964
<i>Hey. Hannah.</i>

202
00:17:26.590 --> 00:17:27.591
Avett.

203
00:17:28.091 --> 00:17:29.300
<i>I've been trying to
reach your husband.</i>

204
00:17:29.301 --> 00:17:31.260
<i>I was hoping you could
help me out with that.</i>

205
00:17:31.261 --> 00:17:33.929
- I'll let him know you called.
- <i>Great.</i>

206
00:17:33.930 --> 00:17:38.018
This whole thing is gonna shake out.
We're innocent. You know that. Hannah.

207
00:17:38.518 --> 00:17:41.937
I mean. I'm... Hell. I'm an entrepreneur.
and your husband's a genius.

208
00:17:41.938 --> 00:17:45.608
I don't have to tell you that.
After all. it is his tech.

209
00:17:45.609 --> 00:17:48.068
I think you mean
the company's tech.

210
00:17:48.069 --> 00:17:49.778
<i>Of course. Of course.</i>

211
00:17:49.779 --> 00:17:53.325
My point is that this whole
thing is clearly a setup.

212
00:17:53.825 --> 00:17:57.369
Okay. and who exactly
is setting you up?

213
00:17:57.370 --> 00:18:00.372
How the hell should I know?
The government? A competitor?

214
00:18:00.373 --> 00:18:04.835
But we gotta beat this. 'cause I have
worked too damn hard for too damn long

215
00:18:04.836 --> 00:18:07.546
to be taken down by
some accounting mishap.

216
00:18:07.547 --> 00:18:11.800
Wait. so is it an accounting
mishap and not a setup?

217
00:18:11.801 --> 00:18:14.596
Are you just saying whatever you
think will get you off the hook?

218
00:18:15.180 --> 00:18:16.264
Excuse me?

219
00:18:16.765 --> 00:18:19.392
<i>Just trying to figure out
what you want here. Avett.</i>

220
00:18:20.518 --> 00:18:22.604
I am trying to
help here. Hannah.

221
00:18:23.563 --> 00:18:25.648
The FBI is coming for Owen next.

222
00:18:25.649 --> 00:18:28.567
and I know he does not wanna
be on the wrong side of this.

223
00:18:28.568 --> 00:18:29.861
Not with his history.

224
00:18:31.821 --> 00:18:34.365
- What history?
- <i>Just have Owen get in touch.</i>

225
00:18:34.366 --> 00:18:36.784
My lawyers have been trying to
reach him and we wanna make sure

226
00:18:36.785 --> 00:18:38.994
that he talks to them before
he talks to anybody else.

227
00:18:38.995 --> 00:18:41.622
<i>We both know that is in
Owen's best interest.</i>

228
00:18:41.623 --> 00:18:45.335
No. I don't know. I'm not
following. Avett. What history?

229
00:18:45.919 --> 00:18:49.589
You really don't know? Then
why'd you skip town. Hannah?

230
00:18:50.423 --> 00:18:51.715
Who says I skipped town?

231
00:18:51.716 --> 00:18:54.135
<i>Just tell Owen he
needs to call me.</i>

232
00:18:55.679 --> 00:18:56.846
What was that about?

233
00:18:58.848 --> 00:19:00.057
Nothing. Don't worry about it.

234
00:19:00.058 --> 00:19:01.892
You know I could actually
hear Avett. so...

235
00:19:01.893 --> 00:19:04.312
I'm just trying to protect
you from this stuff. Bailey.

236
00:19:05.564 --> 00:19:08.108
You can't. No one can.

237
00:19:09.693 --> 00:19:12.320
So how about you just
tell me the truth?

238
00:19:14.489 --> 00:19:19.159
I think Avett was calling to
threaten me. To threaten us.

239
00:19:19.160 --> 00:19:22.914
He sounded guilty. or at least like
he's trying to cover something up.

240
00:19:23.415 --> 00:19:28.253
And he seemed surprised that your dad
disappeared instead of holing up with him.

241
00:19:28.753 --> 00:19:30.338
So he said my dad was guilty?

242
00:19:31.548 --> 00:19:33.216
Certainly wants
us to think that.

243
00:19:34.050 --> 00:19:37.512
And to think he had
something over your father.

244
00:19:41.683 --> 00:19:45.645
Bailey. Avett is just... He's
just trying to cover his own ass.

245
00:19:46.229 --> 00:19:48.981
And for the record. the more people
try to convince me your dad's guilty.

246
00:19:48.982 --> 00:19:52.526
the more I believe he isn't. Maybe
that's naive. but I don't know.

247
00:19:52.527 --> 00:19:54.738
there's something in my
gut that says he's...

248
00:19:55.697 --> 00:20:00.118
He's doing whatever he's
doing for us. For you.

249
00:20:06.833 --> 00:20:09.460
You know. when I said.
to tell me the truth.

250
00:20:09.461 --> 00:20:13.298
I just meant. like. don't
lie about who's on the phone.

251
00:20:14.174 --> 00:20:15.175
Right.

252
00:20:16.843 --> 00:20:17.844
So that was extra?

253
00:20:19.512 --> 00:20:20.513
Yeah.

254
00:20:22.557 --> 00:20:23.767
But in a good way.

255
00:21:24.911 --> 00:21:27.329
- What?
- Something about that tower.

256
00:21:27.330 --> 00:21:30.500
- Does it look familiar?
- More than the last two.

257
00:21:50.854 --> 00:21:52.439
I thought it looked
familiar. but...

258
00:21:53.940 --> 00:21:56.817
- where's the next one?
- We should take a break.

259
00:21:56.818 --> 00:21:59.695
Let's go back to the hotel and
get a fresh start tomorrow.

260
00:21:59.696 --> 00:22:03.491
Fresh start on what.
Hannah? We're nowhere.

261
00:22:03.992 --> 00:22:06.327
We're not nowhere. Look at
what you've already remembered.

262
00:22:06.328 --> 00:22:07.828
What. Hannah? What
have I remembered?

263
00:22:07.829 --> 00:22:10.122
That I went to a football
game with my father.

264
00:22:10.123 --> 00:22:11.666
That doesn't tell us anything.

265
00:22:12.208 --> 00:22:14.084
And for all we know. I might
be remembering it wrong.

266
00:22:14.085 --> 00:22:15.170
It could've been anywhere.

267
00:22:49.037 --> 00:22:50.038
Bailey.

268
00:23:29.661 --> 00:23:30.912
I think it was here.

269
00:23:35.292 --> 00:23:38.294
- You wanna know what now?
- We just need a list of the weddings

270
00:23:38.295 --> 00:23:42.673
that your pastor performed on game
days during the 2011 football season.

271
00:23:42.674 --> 00:23:46.760
I've already handled most of the
legwork. I've got the dates right here.

272
00:23:46.761 --> 00:23:48.722
There were only five home games.

273
00:23:50.849 --> 00:23:55.519
Uh-huh. Yeah. I'm not at liberty
to give out that information.

274
00:23:55.520 --> 00:23:57.856
You're not at liberty? Really?

275
00:24:00.609 --> 00:24:04.028
I think what Bailey is trying to say is
these are pretty unusual circumstances.

276
00:24:04.029 --> 00:24:07.156
- Maybe you could make an exception.
- I am sorry

277
00:24:07.157 --> 00:24:11.161
that your husband is missing. and
I'm sure you're going through a lot.

278
00:24:12.412 --> 00:24:14.747
But that's just not
something we do.

279
00:24:14.748 --> 00:24:17.041
We could sit here
and read the names.

280
00:24:17.042 --> 00:24:18.375
Nothing would leave this room.

281
00:24:18.376 --> 00:24:22.338
I'm afraid we have to protect
the privacy of our congregants.

282
00:24:22.339 --> 00:24:25.591
You cannot be serious. Jesus.
who do you think we are?

283
00:24:25.592 --> 00:24:28.093
I'm going to need to
excuse myself. friends.

284
00:24:28.094 --> 00:24:31.847
We have a Bible study group starting
up. and I need to prepare for that.

285
00:24:31.848 --> 00:24:33.766
Ms. McGovern. Bailey
didn't mean to be rude.

286
00:24:33.767 --> 00:24:36.853
But you heard what's
going on with her father

287
00:24:37.604 --> 00:24:39.271
and family means
everything to us.

288
00:24:39.272 --> 00:24:41.399
You understand that. don't you?

289
00:24:42.901 --> 00:24:44.903
If you were standing here.

290
00:24:45.820 --> 00:24:46.987
what would you hope I'd do?

291
00:24:46.988 --> 00:24:49.074
Because I know I would
try to help you out.

292
00:24:55.080 --> 00:24:56.790
It would be an act
of true kindness.

293
00:25:06.132 --> 00:25:07.425
The names can't leave this room.

294
00:25:08.426 --> 00:25:09.802
Go on. have a seat.

295
00:25:09.803 --> 00:25:11.303
Thank you. seriously.

296
00:25:11.304 --> 00:25:13.473
Don't thank me. Thank
your stepmother.

297
00:25:19.604 --> 00:25:21.523
Hey. I gotta take this.

298
00:25:24.234 --> 00:25:25.943
- Hey.
- <i>Where have you been?</i>

299
00:25:25.944 --> 00:25:27.027
Sorry. it's been...

300
00:25:27.028 --> 00:25:29.947
<i>You can't ask for my help
and then just disappear.</i>

301
00:25:29.948 --> 00:25:31.533
<i>I got it. What's up?</i>

302
00:25:32.033 --> 00:25:33.785
The Shop COO just got indicted.

303
00:25:36.204 --> 00:25:40.125
- Jordan?
- How closely did Owen work with him?

304
00:25:40.834 --> 00:25:42.419
Jordan was Avett's
number two. so...

305
00:25:43.003 --> 00:25:44.254
- Closely.
- <i>Yeah.</i>

306
00:25:45.338 --> 00:25:48.340
Hannah. I gotta be honest. It's
not looking real good for Owen.

307
00:25:48.341 --> 00:25:50.385
- <i>If I were his lawyer...</i>
- Well. you're not.

308
00:25:51.344 --> 00:25:54.806
Yep. you're right. And frankly. I
don't give a shit about your husband.

309
00:25:55.515 --> 00:25:59.476
But I do care about you. You
need to protect yourself here.

310
00:25:59.477 --> 00:26:03.314
<i>The FBI is asking for an interview.
You have to sit with them.</i>

311
00:26:03.315 --> 00:26:07.444
I know. I just... I need you
to buy me one more day. Jake.

312
00:26:10.363 --> 00:26:13.157
Pissing off the FBI
is not a good idea.

313
00:26:13.158 --> 00:26:15.284
<i>I know how they operate
in cases like this.</i>

314
00:26:15.285 --> 00:26:17.077
They could charge
you with obstruction.

315
00:26:17.078 --> 00:26:19.496
They could try and charge
you as an accessory.

316
00:26:19.497 --> 00:26:21.332
Not to mention leaving
Owen's kid vulnerable

317
00:26:21.333 --> 00:26:23.208
to a custody claim
from extended family.

318
00:26:23.209 --> 00:26:25.337
No. Owen doesn't
have extended family.

319
00:26:26.129 --> 00:26:27.130
That you know of.

320
00:26:28.298 --> 00:26:30.424
Have you heard anything from
your private investigator?

321
00:26:30.425 --> 00:26:32.801
<i>He said he'd have something
by the end of day.</i>

322
00:26:32.802 --> 00:26:34.012
Avett called.

323
00:26:35.263 --> 00:26:37.806
He made it seem like he knew
something damaging about Owen.

324
00:26:37.807 --> 00:26:40.226
About his history. I mean.

325
00:26:40.227 --> 00:26:44.647
<i>This is exactly what I'm saying. If
Owen was involved in something shady.</i>

326
00:26:44.648 --> 00:26:48.359
you need to make it obvious to the Feds
that you didn't have the slightest idea.

327
00:26:48.360 --> 00:26:51.153
<i>You need to cooperate. so they
believe you're telling the truth</i>

328
00:26:51.154 --> 00:26:52.613
<i>no matter what comes out.</i>

329
00:26:52.614 --> 00:26:53.864
I am telling the truth.

330
00:26:53.865 --> 00:26:56.743
Then let me set something up
with them for tomorrow morning.

331
00:26:57.702 --> 00:27:00.412
I can come up to SF if you
want counsel in person.

332
00:27:00.413 --> 00:27:03.082
You want me to make
up numbers and dates?

333
00:27:03.083 --> 00:27:04.333
- No. it's not...
- I gotta go.

334
00:27:04.334 --> 00:27:06.335
- Wait. Hannah...
- <i>Get me one more day. Jake.</i>

335
00:27:06.336 --> 00:27:07.586
- Please.
- Please lower your voice.

336
00:27:07.587 --> 00:27:09.338
- This is wrong.
- Could you check your tone?

337
00:27:09.339 --> 00:27:11.423
It doesn't make sense.
Check in another book.

338
00:27:11.424 --> 00:27:12.883
- No. the book is not wrong.
- I was here.

339
00:27:12.884 --> 00:27:15.219
- Look at every one of these dates. you...
- Can you check it again?

340
00:27:15.220 --> 00:27:16.971
- What's going on?
- No. I checked it twice.

341
00:27:16.972 --> 00:27:19.306
It doesn't make any
sense. I was here.

342
00:27:19.307 --> 00:27:21.600
According to my
records. we were closed

343
00:27:21.601 --> 00:27:23.936
for construction in
the fall of 2011.

344
00:27:23.937 --> 00:27:28.190
Our doors shut on September 1st
and they didn't reopen until March.

345
00:27:28.191 --> 00:27:30.901
There was no services. no
ceremonies. no weddings.

346
00:27:30.902 --> 00:27:32.861
I was here. I know I was here.

347
00:27:32.862 --> 00:27:34.572
Well. maybe you
have the year wrong.

348
00:27:34.573 --> 00:27:36.282
No. we don't have
the year wrong.

349
00:27:36.283 --> 00:27:38.826
- It had to have been 2011.
- Then it wasn't here.

350
00:27:38.827 --> 00:27:41.036
Are there any other churches
that look like this nearby?

351
00:27:41.037 --> 00:27:42.581
I don't think so.

352
00:27:47.794 --> 00:27:49.169
Why don't you leave
me your number.

353
00:27:49.170 --> 00:27:51.005
and I'll call you if
I remember anything.

354
00:27:51.006 --> 00:27:52.631
Like you're gonna
remember anything.

355
00:27:52.632 --> 00:27:55.385
- Bailey.
- Whatever. I'm so done with this.

356
00:28:02.225 --> 00:28:05.978
- I'm sorry. I appreciate your help.
- It's fine.

357
00:28:05.979 --> 00:28:07.689
I know it isn't me
she's angry with.

358
00:28:09.733 --> 00:28:14.361
If you think of anything. even if
it feels unimportant. please call.

359
00:28:14.362 --> 00:28:15.447
I will.

360
00:28:18.533 --> 00:28:20.368
Who does this to his family?

361
00:28:21.578 --> 00:28:22.829
Someone without a choice.

362
00:28:51.608 --> 00:28:54.444
- What you doing there. pal?
- Who the fuck are you?

363
00:29:01.034 --> 00:29:03.328
- I'm a friend of Owen's.
- You're a friend.

364
00:29:04.454 --> 00:29:05.705
Colleague. more like.

365
00:29:07.415 --> 00:29:09.959
Eric Cousins. Head of
security for The Shop.

366
00:29:09.960 --> 00:29:11.335
So Avett sent you?

367
00:29:11.336 --> 00:29:13.588
He's just concerned
about Owen's well-being.

368
00:29:14.714 --> 00:29:16.074
Is that what he's
concerned about?

369
00:29:17.342 --> 00:29:18.425
I'll tell you what.

370
00:29:18.426 --> 00:29:20.844
Why don't you let Avett know
that if he sends anyone else.

371
00:29:20.845 --> 00:29:23.056
I'll see to it that Judge
Bari revokes his bail.

372
00:29:27.978 --> 00:29:30.021
Now. go on. Get going.

373
00:30:50.852 --> 00:30:52.687
Where'd you go. Hannah?

374
00:31:27.180 --> 00:31:28.223
Jesus.

375
00:31:43.738 --> 00:31:46.198
Do you know the secret
of a good grilled cheese?

376
00:31:46.199 --> 00:31:48.994
Coating the bread in
mayo instead of butter.

377
00:31:50.120 --> 00:31:52.560
Please tell me that's not how
you make grilled cheese at home.

378
00:31:53.164 --> 00:31:54.164
Afraid so.

379
00:31:54.165 --> 00:31:57.043
That was the one thing I
actually liked about you.

380
00:32:00.171 --> 00:32:02.007
<i>What are you doing here?</i>

381
00:32:05.010 --> 00:32:07.721
So. I know the
churches were a bust...

382
00:32:09.389 --> 00:32:12.601
but I was thinking maybe we can
still find a record of the wedding.

383
00:32:13.184 --> 00:32:15.477
- We could head down to the <i>Statesman</i>.
- The <i>Statesman</i>?

384
00:32:15.478 --> 00:32:17.479
It's a local paper.
Jules has a contact.

385
00:32:17.480 --> 00:32:19.982
I thought we could go
through the archives

386
00:32:19.983 --> 00:32:22.318
and look at the wedding
announcements in 2011.

387
00:32:22.319 --> 00:32:25.446
No. We're not gonna
find anything here.

388
00:32:25.447 --> 00:32:28.324
Well. at the very least. I want
to go to the US Marshals' office.

389
00:32:28.325 --> 00:32:31.328
Ask someone what Deputy Bradford
was doing on our doorstep.

390
00:32:31.995 --> 00:32:34.163
Why? What difference is
it gonna make. Hannah?

391
00:32:34.164 --> 00:32:37.374
Dad's gone. He hasn't called
or emailed or anything.

392
00:32:37.375 --> 00:32:38.709
He doesn't wanna be found.

393
00:32:38.710 --> 00:32:42.630
Okay. but there may be
a good reason for that.

394
00:32:42.631 --> 00:32:44.298
Something we need to find out.

395
00:32:44.299 --> 00:32:46.759
No. you're just making shit up
now to make yourself feel better.

396
00:32:46.760 --> 00:32:49.221
But we're not gonna feel better.
'cause this fucking sucks.

397
00:32:50.180 --> 00:32:53.432
Whatever's going on. he clearly was
into something he didn't tell us about.

398
00:32:53.433 --> 00:32:56.352
And me and you playing <i>Encyclopedia
Brown</i> isn't going to change anything.

399
00:32:56.353 --> 00:32:57.728
- Don't you get that?
- Slow down.

400
00:32:57.729 --> 00:33:00.649
No. no. You're not hearing
me. I just... I wanna go home.

401
00:33:01.650 --> 00:33:02.733
<i>No. Dad.</i>

402
00:33:02.734 --> 00:33:03.902
You're not hearing me.

403
00:33:11.952 --> 00:33:13.161
<i>What's going on?</i>

404
00:33:13.662 --> 00:33:16.872
Bobby's parents invited
Bailey on their boat.

405
00:33:16.873 --> 00:33:17.958
You said "no."

406
00:33:18.500 --> 00:33:23.379
About as quickly as you can say
it. I mean. she's barely 16.

407
00:33:23.380 --> 00:33:25.215
They'll have
minimal supervision.

408
00:33:25.715 --> 00:33:26.716
On a boat?

409
00:33:28.760 --> 00:33:29.761
It's a big boat.

410
00:33:31.346 --> 00:33:33.265
Well. I think that's
a reasonable decision.

411
00:33:33.765 --> 00:33:34.766
Yeah.

412
00:33:36.226 --> 00:33:39.061
So why are you down here
sitting in the dark.

413
00:33:39.062 --> 00:33:40.814
clutching her piggy bank?

414
00:33:43.525 --> 00:33:47.028
Her grandmother bought her
this the day she was born.

415
00:33:52.325 --> 00:33:54.911
Soon I'm not going to be
able to tell her "no."

416
00:33:56.621 --> 00:33:58.872
She's gonna leave. do
exactly what she wants.

417
00:33:58.873 --> 00:34:03.837
and I don't think I ever
fully thought about that.

418
00:34:05.505 --> 00:34:07.299
Or maybe I just
didn't let myself.

419
00:34:09.134 --> 00:34:10.635
Ah. man.

420
00:34:18.309 --> 00:34:22.021
There's gonna come a time when I won't
be able to keep her safe anymore.

421
00:34:24.274 --> 00:34:25.567
Not from anything.

422
00:34:31.573 --> 00:34:32.573
Hey.

423
00:34:33.157 --> 00:34:34.367
How'd the churches pan out?

424
00:34:35.076 --> 00:34:38.871
Not so great. I think we're
gonna head home tomorrow.

425
00:34:38.872 --> 00:34:40.539
<i>Well. I'll be happy to see you.</i>

426
00:34:42.459 --> 00:34:45.003
- <i>What?</i>
- I just...

427
00:34:45.753 --> 00:34:49.172
Bailey is so out of sorts
here. Makes me wonder.

428
00:34:49.173 --> 00:34:52.219
I'm pretty sure Bailey would be
out of sorts wherever she was.

429
00:34:53.094 --> 00:34:55.889
I don't know. I think maybe it's
because we're onto something.

430
00:34:58.266 --> 00:35:01.894
Then again. maybe I'm just trying to avoid
dealing with the shit show back there.

431
00:35:01.895 --> 00:35:03.854
<i>You know. you have
pretty good instincts.</i>

432
00:35:03.855 --> 00:35:07.066
Which is why I haven't spoken
to my husband in three days.

433
00:35:07.067 --> 00:35:08.984
<i>Go easy on yourself. would you?</i>

434
00:35:08.985 --> 00:35:11.987
Not in my nature. Are
you still at work?

435
00:35:11.988 --> 00:35:13.323
I just left. Why?

436
00:35:13.823 --> 00:35:17.952
Could you stop at my place on your
way home? I'm sure it's nothing.

437
00:35:17.953 --> 00:35:21.790
but there's a piggy bank in
Bailey's room I want you to look at.

438
00:35:22.457 --> 00:35:25.335
Piggy bank? Is that some
kind of tech bro euphemism?

439
00:35:26.002 --> 00:35:27.169
I wish.

440
00:35:27.170 --> 00:35:30.631
No. there was this weird file on Owen's
laptop that was password-protected.

441
00:35:30.632 --> 00:35:34.553
and the hint was "L.
Paul." Lady Paul.

442
00:35:35.512 --> 00:35:38.640
which I think is also the
name on the piggy bank.

443
00:35:39.933 --> 00:35:43.561
And I stopped believing in
coincidences about 48 hours ago.

444
00:35:43.562 --> 00:35:45.689
Okay. I'll head there now.

445
00:35:46.273 --> 00:35:47.315
<i>I don't deserve you.</i>

446
00:35:47.816 --> 00:35:48.942
<i>Nobody does.</i>

447
00:35:49.651 --> 00:35:51.027
<i>Call you when I get there.</i>

448
00:36:20.640 --> 00:36:21.766
- Bails?
- <i>Hey.</i>

449
00:36:23.852 --> 00:36:26.313
So. the s'mores worked. Noted.

450
00:36:26.980 --> 00:36:29.232
- <i>What?</i>
- Are you at home?

451
00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:31.025
Open your front door.

452
00:36:31.026 --> 00:36:34.069
I'm actually in Austin.

453
00:36:34.070 --> 00:36:35.947
<i>Austin? Why?</i>

454
00:36:36.531 --> 00:36:40.994
<i>Good question. I don't know.
Hiding out from all my fans.</i>

455
00:36:42.621 --> 00:36:46.374
Well. I hate to break it to you.
but you're no longer trending.

456
00:36:46.958 --> 00:36:48.250
- Really?
- <i>Yep.</i>

457
00:36:48.251 --> 00:36:52.339
Livvy and Alex ended things
in pretty spectacular fashion.

458
00:36:53.048 --> 00:36:54.340
<i>What happened?</i>

459
00:36:54.341 --> 00:36:56.091
Let's just say it involved
a large bottle of Diet Coke

460
00:36:56.092 --> 00:36:57.969
<i>being poured over Alex's head.</i>

461
00:36:59.471 --> 00:37:02.390
I have never been so
relieved to not matter.

462
00:37:03.642 --> 00:37:08.939
Good. So. should I come rescue
you from your wicked stepmother?

463
00:37:10.941 --> 00:37:12.984
She's maybe not the
worst person ever.

464
00:37:13.818 --> 00:37:17.781
<i>I'm sorry. thought I was
talking to Bailey Michaels</i>.

465
00:37:39.761 --> 00:37:40.762
Hello?

466
00:38:24.556 --> 00:38:25.932
What the fuck is this?

467
00:38:51.249 --> 00:38:54.377
Whoever's in here.
I just called 911!

468
00:38:55.337 --> 00:38:56.588
Jules?

469
00:39:01.843 --> 00:39:03.220
What the hell are
you doing here?

470
00:39:03.803 --> 00:39:04.929
I need to talk to Hannah.

471
00:39:04.930 --> 00:39:07.056
What. so you just let
yourself into her house?

472
00:39:07.057 --> 00:39:09.601
Well. the door was wide open.
But it's great to see you too.

473
00:39:11.519 --> 00:39:14.606
- Is she here?
- No. She's not here.

474
00:39:15.690 --> 00:39:18.526
- Well. I need to talk to her.
- God. About what?

475
00:39:20.278 --> 00:39:22.155
I need to tell her directly.

476
00:39:23.240 --> 00:39:25.867
Well. you're going to have to
tell me directly first. Jake.

477
00:39:26.368 --> 00:39:28.286
'Cause I'm the only one
who knows where she is.

478
00:40:38.565 --> 00:40:40.275
Hey. Did you find
the piggy bank?

479
00:40:40.901 --> 00:40:41.902
<i>Yeah.</i>

480
00:40:43.153 --> 00:40:44.154
But...

481
00:40:46.114 --> 00:40:47.365
can Bailey hear you?

482
00:40:48.366 --> 00:40:50.994
No. she's asleep.
Why? What's going on?

483
00:40:52.412 --> 00:40:54.288
Jake's here. I'm
gonna put him on.

484
00:40:54.289 --> 00:40:56.332
<i>What? Why is Jake there?</i>

485
00:40:56.333 --> 00:40:57.417
<i>Hey.</i>

486
00:40:58.335 --> 00:41:00.086
What are you doing in my house?

487
00:41:01.463 --> 00:41:06.259
I wanted to be here. I needed
to tell you this in person.

488
00:41:07.177 --> 00:41:09.137
Tell me what? Jake.

489
00:41:09.930 --> 00:41:15.393
I heard back from my investigator.
It took him a minute because. well.

490
00:41:16.394 --> 00:41:20.065
<i>Owen and Bailey's
histories are inconsistent.</i>

491
00:41:21.358 --> 00:41:23.235
What do you mean inconsistent?

492
00:41:23.902 --> 00:41:27.321
<i>There are several Owen Michaels who
grew up in Newton. Massachusetts.</i>

493
00:41:27.322 --> 00:41:29.907
<i>and a few who graduated
from Princeton University.</i>

494
00:41:29.908 --> 00:41:34.453
But the only Owen Michaels who's
from Newton and went to Princeton

495
00:41:34.454 --> 00:41:37.206
is 78 years old and now
lives with his partner.

496
00:41:37.207 --> 00:41:40.919
Theo Silverstein. in
Provincetown. Massachusetts.

497
00:41:41.711 --> 00:41:42.712
That's not possible.

498
00:41:43.213 --> 00:41:46.549
<i>My guy couldn't find a marriage license
for Owen Michaels or Olivia Miller.</i>

499
00:41:46.550 --> 00:41:49.093
He also couldn't
find any evidence

500
00:41:49.094 --> 00:41:52.138
that Owen and Olivia ever
owned a home in Seattle.

501
00:41:53.223 --> 00:41:54.891
Wait. I don't understand. I...

502
00:41:55.976 --> 00:41:57.936
He couldn't find anything
on Bailey. either.

503
00:41:58.520 --> 00:42:02.231
<i>No Seattle birth certificate of a
Bailey Michaels born in the early 2000s.</i>

504
00:42:02.232 --> 00:42:06.152
<i>No hospital birth records.
No preschool registration</i>.

505
00:42:06.987 --> 00:42:08.904
My guy is pretty sure
there's no record of any kind

506
00:42:08.905 --> 00:42:12.409
for either Owen or Bailey
prior to Sausalito.

507
00:42:12.993 --> 00:42:13.994
Really?

508
00:42:14.744 --> 00:42:20.083
<i>Basically. Owen and Bailey
Michaels don't exist.</i>

509
00:42:33.722 --> 00:42:34.848
Hannah?
